Q1: What feature must the feeder include?
A1: - Manual button
       - Set scheduled times
       - Dispense food for pet at scheduled times
   - Monitor food consumption using sensors
                     Infrared sensors monitor the volume of food
                     Weight sensors monitor the weight of food
   - Alert staff 
                     If food empty
                     If no consumption

Q2: What inputs and outputs are needed?
A2: Inputs 
                 - Set scheduled times
                 - Food consumption such as weight and volume
                 - Manual button
Outputs 
                - Food dispensing
                - Alerts about food consumption and eaten situation




Q3: What are possible assumptions or limitations?
A2: Single pet food can be supported
        If have two or more pets, it cannot alert which one has eaten this food
